.el .ds Aq '
.TH dkp-install 1  "install 0.2.0" 
.SH NAME
dkp\-install \- Install a pack from the registry
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdkp install\fR [\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-\-url\fR] [\fB\-\-checksums\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-\-sig\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-\-audience\fR] [\fB\-\-pubkey\fR] [\fB\-g\fR|\fB\-\-global\fR] [\fB\-\-out\fR] [\fB\-\-token\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-verify\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fINAME\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Install a pack from the registry
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR [default: plain]
Output format
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
plain: Human\-readable plain text (default)
.IP \(bu 2
table: Aligned table using comfy\-table
.IP \(bu 2
json: Pretty\-printed JSON
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-url\fR \fI<URL>\fR
Install directly from a URL without involving the registry. Pass \-\-checksums and/or \-\-sig to verify integrity
.TP
\fB\-\-checksums\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Path to a checksums.json for verifying a \-\-url install
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress informational output; print only results
.TP
\fB\-\-sig\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Path to a bundle.sig for verifying a \-\-url install
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Print debug info (schema paths, provider calls, etc.)
.TP
\fB\-\-audience\fR \fI<ID>\fR
Filter content to assets tagged for a specific audience profile
.TP
\fB\-\-pubkey\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Publisher Ed25519 public key for verifying a \-\-url install (hex, base64, or raw 32\-byte file)
.TP
\fB\-g\fR, \fB\-\-global\fR
Install to global store (~/.dkp/packs/)
.TP
\fB\-\-out\fR \fI<DIR>\fR
Install to a custom directory
.TP
\fB\-\-token\fR \fI<KEY>\fR
Registry API token
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-verify\fR
Skip signature verification for registry installs (NOT RECOMMENDED)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.TP
[\fINAME\fR]
Pack name, e.g. @example/nutrition\-for\-men or @example/pack@1.2.0. Omit to install all packs from dkp.lock
.SH VERSION
v0.2.0
